This paper deals with the detection of digital retouching of face images, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of autoencoders and machine learning algorithms for classification suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.MM) and learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the potential for this technology to be used in security and forensics, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the use of image processing techniques and algorithms for feature extraction suggests that it could also belong to the information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category.
